      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Amoud Foundation's impact is characterized by its low cost-per-beneficiary, which is estimated at <cite id=\"11\">$3.67 per person</cite>, a metric considered exceptional for the humanitarian sector. This efficiency is supported by a <cite id=\"12\">leadership score of 100/100</cite> from Charity Navigator, reflecting a highly capable management team. Furthermore, the foundation has shown impressive growth, achieving a <cite id=\"13\">3-year revenue CAGR of 18.6%</cite>, which indicates increasing donor trust and expanding capacity to address crises in the Horn of Africa."
      ],
      "summary": "founded in 1998, Amoud Foundation has established itself as a critical lifeline for vulnerable populations in the Horn of Africa, specifically focusing on <cite id=\"1\">Somaliland, Somalia, Ethiopia, and Djibouti</cite>. The organization manages a robust portfolio of humanitarian programs, including the oversight of <cite id=\"2\">15 orphan centers and two specialized schools</cite> for deaf and blind students. Financially, the foundation operates with exceptional efficiency, reporting <cite id=\"3\">$9,535,194 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 tax year. A hallmark of their operational model is the high percentage of funds reaching the field; the organization maintains a <cite id=\"4\">89.3% program expense ratio</cite>, which significantly exceeds the <cite id=\"5\">industry standard of 75%</cite>. This lean structure is further evidenced by their fundraising efficiency, which stands at <cite id=\"6\">$0.00 per $1 raised</cite>, ensuring that donor contributions are not eroded by high administrative or marketing costs. Beyond orphan care, the foundation executes large-scale interventions in <cite id=\"7\">water security, emergency food aid, and healthcare</cite>, leveraging a direct service delivery model that minimizes intermediary costs and maximizes local impact.",
